    "patterns_used": [
      { "pattern": "Orchestration Saga", "rationale": "Centralizes saga coordination in a single orchestrator rather than choreography. With 4 sequential steps and strict reverse-order compensation, an orchestrator makes the control flow explicit, testable, and debuggable. Choreography would scatter the compensation logic across 4 services, making failure reasoning much harder." },
      { "pattern": "Compensating Transaction", "rationale": "Each forward step has a semantic inverse (cancel, release, refund, unassign). These are not database rollbacks — they are domain-level operations that undo the business effect of the prior step." },
