      "gains": "Crash recovery — orchestrator can resume or compensate from last known state after restart.",
      "sacrifices": "One extra write per step (latency cost). For 4 steps, this adds 4 writes to the critical path.",
      "alternatives_considered": ["In-memory saga state with event sourcing replay. More complex but avoids per-step writes. Overkill for this flow size."]
